headline: Saudia Group Selects GE Aerospace GEnx-1B Engines to Power New 787 Dreamliners
summary: A multi-year agreement advancing aerospace localization in the Kingdom SaudiaGroup x GEAerospace - Signing Ceremony Signing ceremony for SaudiaGroup x GEAerospace. WASHINGTON, Nov. 24, 2025 (GLOBE NEWSWIRE) -- Saudia Group, one of the largest aviation conglomerates in the MENA region, has announced a strategic agreement with GE Aerospace (NYSE: GE) to equip Saudia, the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia’s national flag carrier, with GEnx-1B engines for its 2023 order of 39 Boeing 787-9 and 787-10 aircraft.
